{
  "texts": [
    "They also introduce a new training technique, called Stochastic Depth, that improves training speed by randomly dropping network layers during training.",
    "The model is evaluated on numerous benchmark datasets and presented with fewer parameters and less computation than previous models.The architecture of VGGNet, a deep CNN that achieves better performance on the ImageNet dataset.",
    "The network consists of a series of convolutional layers with small filters and max-pooling layers, followed by several fully connected layers [24].",
    "The implementation investigates the effect of increasing the depth of the network on performance and find that deeper networks perform better, but with diminishing returns beyond a certain depth.",
    "They also compare their network to other state-of-the-art networks and demonstrate superior performance.The AlexNet involves of many convolutional layers with small filters, max-pooling layers, and many fully connected layers."
  ]
}